Package com.cornell.opencomm.jingleimpl

Interface Summary
DescriptionElementType.MediaTypes Contains various media type names
JingleIQPacket.AttributeActionValues This interface lists all possible values that the action attribute of a Jingle Element can have.
PayloadElementType.SupportedPayloadType This interface lists all current supported payload-type(codec) For future development, add new supported payload-type here
 

Class Summary
BaseElementType This is the base class to represent all elements as defined by XEP-0166, XEP-0167, XEP-0177 This contains utility functions needed by classes that represent each xml element.
CandidateElementType This Class encapsulates a Candidate Element as described in XEP-0166 (Jingle), XEP-0176 (ICE UDP) and XEP-0177 (Jingle RAW UDP) The class also declares attributes and elements that would be needed during ICE Negotiations.
ContentElementType This class models the Content Element of a Jingle element based from XEP-0166
DescriptionElementType This class models a Description element as described in the XEP-0167
JingleIQPacket This class models a Jingle Element as defined by XEP-0166 This class is based on the earlier Jingle code being used by the network team and is an attempt to make it more general.
JingleIQProvider This class handles the parsing of incoming IQ packets.
PayloadElementType This class models the PayloadElementType from the XEP-0166
ReasonElementType This class models the Reason Element of a Jingle element based from XEP-0166
TransportElementType This class models the Transport Element which is contained in a Description element
